messages.description: Making the sign involves forming a circle with the thumb and index finger while extending the other three fingers upward. The sign is used to ask whether everything is OK when it is the initial signal. Otherwise, it is used as a reply indicating everything is OK.
The hand signal for 'I am OK' is often accompanied by a slight nod of the head to emphasize the meaning.

The slow movement of a flashlight in a moderate-sized circle (in either direction), when it is the initial signal, can be used to ask another diver whether they are OK. Otherwise, the signal is used as a reply to indicate 'Yes, I am OK'.
The sign is used to communicate to another diver that they must pause and cease any ongoing activity.
Nodding is associated with indicating agreement, affirmation, or understanding. When a diver nods, it typically signifies a positive response or acknowledgment.
The signals for 'Emergency' and 'Attention' are performed by vigorous flashing movements of a diver's light beam in a horizontal or vertical direction.
